  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Background: Genetics is suggested to play a critical role in the development of Behçet's
      disease (BD). Shared phenotypic features requires an approach to the differential diagnosis
      from periodic febrile syndromes particularly from mevalonate kinase deficiency related
      diseases. We planned to study for evaluating the frequency of mutations and their clinical
      significance in mevalonate kinase gene in Turkish patients with Behçet's disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
